Reasoning: The paper proposes a framework for training deep directed generative models using energy-based probability estimation. This involves the use of deep neural networks to represent the energy function and the generator, which are both key components of the proposed framework. Given the focus on deep learning and generative models, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
